HIGHWAYS: Designates certain portions of Louisiana highways
1 AN ACT
2 To designate a portion of Louisiana Highway 182 in the city of Jeanerette, between
3 Hubertville Road and Canal Street, as the "Berwick 'BJ' LeJeune, Jr. Memorial
4 Highway"; to designate a portion of Louisiana Highway 182 between the cities of
5 Jeanerette and Sorrel, as the "Ret. Judge Richard T. 'Dickey' Haik, Sr. Highway"; to
6 provide for implementation; and to provide for related matters.
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. The portion of Louisiana Highway 182 in the city of Jeanerette, between
9 Hubertville Road and Canal Street, shall be known and is hereby designated as the "Berwick
10 'BJ' LeJeune, Jr. Memorial Highway".
11 Section 2. The portion of Louisiana Highway 182 between the cities of Jeanerette
12 and Sorrel, from Louisiana Highway 671 to Louisiana Highway 318, shall be known and is
13 hereby designated as the "Ret. Judge Richard T. 'Dickey' Haik, Sr. Highway".
14 Section 3. The Department of Transportation and Development or its contractors are
15 hereby directed to erect and maintain appropriate signage reflecting these designations
16 provided local or private monies are received by the department equal to the department's
17 actual cost for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and installation of the signage, not to
18 exceed the sum of seven hundred fifty dollars per sign.
