HB 657 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Bryant
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 182 in the city of Jeanerette, between Hubertville Rd. and
Canal St., as the "Berwick 'BJ' LeJeune, Jr. Memorial Highway".
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 182 between the cities of Jeanerette and Sorrel, from La.
Hwy. 671 to La. Hwy. 318, as the "Ret. Judge Richard T. 'Dickey' Haik, Sr. Highway".
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) to erect and maintain
appropriate signage reflecting the hwy. designations provided local or private monies are
received by the DOTD equal to its actual costs for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and
installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign.
